verbLexeme: 1. To drive a car into a parking space and leave it there. English = park.
2. To drive a car backwards usually in order to park it. English = back up, reverse park.
nominalLexeme: 1. An area or a building where people can leave their cars. English = car park, parking lot.
2. An individual space for a car on the side of a road or within a car park. English = park, parking space.
oldEntry: Popular explanation: one vehicle parking behind another.
